Tata Communications Plans to Invest S$440 Million in Singapore

-- B y   S i m e o n   B e n n e t t
-- 
2011-05-12T01:23:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/tata-communications-plans-to-invest-s-440-million-in-singapore.html
Tata Communications Ltd. (TCOM)  plans to
invest S$440 million ($356 million) over four years in
 Singapore , the company said in a statement yesterday.  Tata Communications, based in  Mumbai , also said it plans to
increase staff in the city-state by 60 percent in the same
period.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Simeon Bennett in Singapore at 
 sbennett9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
